channel.name: Unable to create a tx for a contract

messages.content:
I have deployed a contract to Testworld: https://minascan.io/testworld/account/B62qpbsHc4anQXXwxk9ESdkBeAoKdqJYxhZSbckhcWk68jKS62y996A/zkApp . I then followed https://docs.minaprotocol.com/zkapps/tutorials/zkapp-ui-with-react to try to create a UI.

Unfortunately, I can't get transactions to work: `getAccount: Could not find account for public key B62qpbsHc4anQXXwxk9ESdkBeAoKdqJYxhZSbckhcWk68jKS62y996A`. Here's the failing line: https://github.com/microbecode/zk-agecheck/blob/ed2593c0dfbdd6c2efb7a93da3293dde73cf69bd/frontend/src/pages/index.tsx#L188 

I had to remove the use of all of the background workers, because a lot of things simply failed if I tried using those. So now I just issue the required(?) commands from the UI code directly - most likely I do some things too many times, since I'm not sure what all is needed.

Any ideas what could be the problem? I'm definitely calling `fetchAccount` (multiple times) to get the contract account, and it definitely exists.

messages.content: Have you switched your Auro wallet to Testworld2?
fair question. Yes. But my wallet isn't even prompted (yet).
Is it connected to your app? Seems like the problem is in Auro
yes. checked and I have the latest Auro version.

It seems like your contract is not deployed. The deployed contract on minascan has zkApp Details: https://minascan.io/testworld/account/B62qpiD9ZWPi1JCx7hd4XcRujM1qc5jCADhhJVzTm3zZBWBpyRr3NFT/zkApp?type=zk-acc

oh darn. Had no idea.
Now that I look at the deployment tx again, it seems to have failed with "Invalid_fee_excess" (https://minascan.io/testworld/tx/5JuB8sSK1g7WGzHYtkStzJP76yVDFHhVGtCskzcLXXsVDLcmH1P3?type=zk-tx). I just don't understand why the error comes. The account sending it hasn't deployed anything else, as far as I can tell.
I'll just try again with a fresh account. I've tried that maybe 5 times already, but with Berkeley. Maybe I have better luck with testworld..
in fact, I don't think I've ever managed to deploy something on Mina 🙂 I'm just missing some fundamental pieces of my understanding.
What is the line on your code for contract deployment? I would check for AccountUpdate line first
I deploy with `zk deploy` in the `circuits` folder in the repo
I see only local deploy there
hmm? the `config.json`points to testworld
Yes, but I don't see where zk-age-check is used
well when I do `zk deploy` it asks whether I want to deploy that, and I say yes.
Aaaah! You're using cli to deploy
tried with fresh fee payer and fresh deployer acc. requested faucet funds to both. still same error. https://minascan.io/testworld/tx/5JuCHNMxvk7fy3JstAKfLPdVkEfeTYibh7wkBKBehiMkkMy513LW?type=zk-tx

but anyway, this goes besides the original topic of this thread. I'll try searching for more possible answers to this error message or start a new thread. this thread's original problem was just related to an incomplete contract deployment.

would love it if you have ideas on how to solve this, of course, meanwhile.
thanks for all the assistance so far!

The first error is “Cancelled”.  The second error is “Invalid fee excess”. The reason there is a fee excess seems to be that the deployment is cancelled, so there is no new account creation fee spent.
Idk wtf “Cancelled” means though
On my Mac, the deployment transaction for your contract is successful: https://minascan.io/testworld/tx/5Ju2RpNgftSubY7eQYVfj6CRFrbkjuZijT7Ur7Y31jwxwbry59KM?type=zk-tx
I use code, not cli
That makes sense
You can try with this address: https://minascan.io/testworld/account/B62qpZzJphwsr6i1ifszvebAZPvkQpUTnWus6rX68jPiPJejMuQhVYd/zkApp?type=zk-acc
I was going to suggest removing `requireSignature` from init as that could be a culprit.   If you use a custom deploy script, you can add the sig.

Removed `requireSignature`, rebuilt and tried again. same error. stupid shit.
I'll try with code, thanks.
@ymekuria seems like a zkapp-cli bug ^

Well, using your code @45930 I get `Error: It seems you're running multiple provers concurrently within the same JavaScript thread, which, at the moment, is not supported and would lead to bugs`. Checked my packages, only one o1js as peer dependency, cleared node_modules, nothing helps. Using latest o1js.

I guess I'll just have to try again tomorrow. nothing works today for me.
Well, in Mina ecosystem we can fix it too and made that everything will work for you)

my problem was that I was importing the circuit code from another npm project (`circuits` folder). now that I tried having the code in the same project, the deployment goes through. Although now my contract has "Not activated" stamp, no idea why. https://minascan.io/testworld/account/B62qjPvnKKqtbfpWNL3rGfNLwbFkP5X6DB1DTTumNMCDWcWnRcdpBa7/zkApp?type=zk-acc
Even requested faucet funds to the contract, didn't help.
Interacting with the contract fails with the already familiar "could not find account".

I see that on github there is still an old address in the code:
https://github.com/microbecode/zk-agecheck/blob/master/frontend/src/pages/index.tsx#L25

Re not activated, it will go away in some time automatically,

pushed new code with new address being used.
does this just mean that a deployed contract can't be used until "not activated" magically disappears at some point?
Anyway. the "not activated" seems to have now disappeared. Unfortunately, the transaction still fails with the same reason as originally. I see the "requireSignature" line is still enabled in the deployment code - will try again with that disabled.
Auro isn't involved in this at all. I provide a private key in the code.
Where do you send transaction in your code?

ah yes, sorry, I was talking about the deployment part.
The transaction sending is here. https://github.com/microbecode/zk-agecheck/blob/master/frontend/src/pages/index.tsx#L172 . Auro isn't prompted before the error happens. I'll try Auro individually
Auro manual transfer works. But zkapp tx doesn't.
this is the zkapp without the "requireSignature" contract line. https://minascan.io/testworld/account/B62qjScikFVx1CeVRazFkcaSvkDfy8igZyMxQgmPQGbjHTmmcQFkEgP/txs
What is ...EgP account?
my previous message.
From code, the transaction to your contract has been sent successfully: https://minascan.io/testworld/tx/5JugHeENo96QSLA2tp5BZ43Pparv8qHAPKJwB3M9eYV2U3JQtYCV?type=zk-tx
Try to print tx.toPretty()
the error happens before I get the tx object
sorry, I don't quite understand what you mean with this. I don't think any of my txs have succeeded
error comes in `.minimumAge.get()`
well I can't prettify the tx object because it explodes before I get the object 🙂
btw, I really appreciate you spending your time on this.
darn. I think that did it. I'm sure I tried that already a few times, but I think it was with some version of the code from yesterday.
Auro is prompted and I get "insufficient balance" even if there's almost 300 mina, but that's a separate topic
thanks a lot!
Add fetchAccount for sender account
it's there. but I'll go through all that again
ah right, it's not there because I don't initialize the state properly, because I took shortcuts.

`Auro is prompted and I get "insufficient balance"`
Can you give me a screenshot of this? Does it appear every time? It just happened once?
Oh no worries, it was just because I had failed to fetchAccount. Everything's ok now. Thanks
